channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Baseball Great Willie Mays Passes Away at 93
Israel on the ballot in Westchester as activists slam 'Squad' incumbent amid reported photo flap
item.description: Rep. Jamaal Bowman, the "Squad member" and former principal, continues to be under fire for his stance on the Israel-Palestinian conflict.

item.title: Trump-Backed McGuire Leads Rep. Bob Good in Race Too Close to Call
item.description: One of America's most conservative congressmen was locked in a tight renomination battle against an opponent endorsed by former President Donald Trump in Virginia's primary election Tuesday.

item.title: Apology Not Accepted - Within Hours of Being Blasted Online, France Overturns Israeli Ban at Defense Show
'Political pandering': GOP lawmakers rip Biden's 'mass amnesty' order as election-year ploy
item.description: Republican lawmakers are criticizing the Biden administration for a plan to grant "mass amnesty" to migrant spouses of U.S. citizens.

item.title: Lawsuits Challenge EPA Rule on Heavy-Duty Truck Emissions
item.description: A coalition of organizations representing the petroleum, biofuel, farming, and independent trucking industries have joined in filing federal lawsuits against the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) regarding restrictive pollution standards on heavy-duty vehicles.

item.title: Trump-Backed GOP Senate Candidate Hung Cao Wins Virginia Primary, Will Face Tim Kaine in November
Legal experts say gag order in Trump case is 'untethered' to 'rationale' after court order
item.description: Legal experts say the gag order against former President Trump is "untethered" to "rationale" after his unprecedented criminal trial in New York.

item.title: Abbott Increases Reward for Information on Juneteenth Shooting
item.description: Texas GOP Gov. Greg Abbott is offering up to $10,000 as a reward for information regarding a fatal shooting at a Juneteenth celebration over the weekend.

item.title: Video Surfaces of Justin Timberlake Lecturing Britney Spears on Alcohol After He Is Arrested for DUI
Biden team argues that all unflattering videos of him are fake, but that’s not true
item.description: Team Biden has been working overtime to brush off video that's renewed questions of the president's mental acuity – questions they can't expect to hide from forever.

item.title: Senate Passes Bill to Support Advanced Nuclear Energy Deployment
item.description: The Senate on Tuesday passed a bill to accelerate the deployment of nuclear energy capacity, including by speeding permitting and creating new incentives for advanced nuclear reactor technologies. Expanding nuclear power has broad bipartisan support, with Democrats seeing it ...

item.title: Greg Gutfeld Puts Biden/Media Collusion on 'Cheap Fakes' Scandal in Perspective As Only He Can
Newsom seeks to restrict students' cellphone use in schools: 'Harming the mental health of our youth'
item.description: California Gov. Gavin Newsom announced Tuesday he wants to limit students' smartphone use during the school day over its impact on their mental health.

item.title: Sen. Paul to Newsmax: Fauci Lied on 'Rachel Maddow Show'
item.description: Sen. Rand Paul, R-Ky., criticized Dr. Anthony Fauci during an interview with Newsmax on Tuesday, accusing him of lying about the nature of research funded by the National Institutes of Health (NIH) while he appeared on "The Rachel Maddow Show."
